cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SI

This paper discusses bibliometric indicators and their impact on the scientific ecosystem, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, the focus on journal impact factors and their limitations suggests that cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are likely sub-categories. Additionally, the discussion of adverse effects on individual behaviors and the research enterprise could be relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the mention of alternative journal-based indicators suggests that cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) may also be a relevant sub-category.
